'''''Star Wars'' 78''' is the seventy-eighth issue in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of comics.

==Publisher's summary==
''A flashback sequence involving an old friend of Luke's from the planet of ice, Hoth''.<ref name="ma12">''Marvel Age'' #1 and #2</ref>

==Plot summary==
Some time after the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]], and [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Barlon Hightower/Legends|Barlon Hightower]] leave [[Arbra/Legends|Arbra]] to investigate a crippled freighter which appears to have come from [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]. Luke believes that [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], here described as an old friend who grew up with him on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], is aboard. When they come aboard, the ship appears to be abandoned, but the ship's log contains a recording of Wedge's voice. The recording tells the story of how Wedge and fellow pilot [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]] survived the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]].

They were stranded there for months, fending off the deadly cold and [[Wampa/Legends|Wampa]] attacks. One day, when Wedge went out hunting for [[Ice scrabbler/Legends|ice scrabblers]], a group of scavengers led by [[Arns Grimraker]] came across the wounded Janson and killed him. Wedge avenged his friend by stealing the scavengers' ship, and leading their pursuing ships into the path of the [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighters]] who had been left behind in the [[Hoth system/Legends|Hoth system]] to search for [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] stragglers. The tape ends with Wedge noting that his vessel is now adrift.

However, it turns out that Wedge is still alive, and was merely outside the transport doing exterior repairs. Wedge is reunited with his friend Luke, and the four Rebels return to Arbra to celebrate.

==Continuity==
{{Quote|I always did like spinnin' a good yarn!|Wedge Antilles|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 78">[[Star Wars (1977) 78|''Star Wars'' (1977) 78]]</ref>}}
This issue greatly contradicts established [[canon]]. Wedge Antilles is stranded on Hoth in this issue, although he escapes the Battle of Hoth in the [[Star Wars (radio)|radio adaptation]] of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], and appears in ''[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]''. The backstory of [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]] is also mistakenly applied to Wedge Antilles here. Finally, Wes Janson dies in this issue, despite reappearing in many of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron's]] later adventures. The [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]] article ''[[Hoth: Under the Ice]]'', however, has brought aspects of this story back into canon, and identified the rest as a tall tale Wedge Antilles tells new recruits.

During Wedge's story, he says, "Not that morning was much better&mdash;but at least the suns were out to make things seem warmer." This seems to imply that the [[Hoth system/Legends|Hoth system]] has a [[Binary star/Legends|binary star]], something that is non-canon.

''Hoth Stuff!'' was originally intended to appear in [[Star Wars (1977) 73|issue 73]], and then [[Star Wars (1977) 74|issue 74]].<ref name="ma12" /> This issue was originally scheduled to feature [[Star Wars (1977) 79|''The Big Con'']], which appeared in the [[Star Wars (1977) 79|next issue]].<ref name="ma" />

